http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/University-technological-meet-on-January-8-9/article13980168.ece

Amal Jyothi College of Engineering at Kanjirappally will host KETCON - 16, the first technological conference of A.P.J. Abdul Kalam Technological University (KTU) and Techfest organised by the Kerala State Council for Science, Technology and Environment (KSCSTE) on January 8 and 9. An official release issued here said that the joint programme will focus on ‘Technology for sustainability’. The conference will have paper and project presentations.The aim of the initiative is to step up the innovative ideas and projects among engineering students and enhance the scientific temper in high school and higher secondary students. Education Minister P. K. Abdu Rabb will inaugurate the programme on January 8.Suresh Das, Executive vice-president of KSCSTE, will preside over the function.